reviews: Can't hear my girlfriend talk, 10/10 would buy again.

review_title: Overpriced fans with good RGB, decent software and horrible cable management.
reviews:
Please note: If you have issues with one of your fans and you purchased the 3 pack, you will be required to send all 3 fans back.

The moment I opened the box and saw all of the cables I knew right away that this was going to be an absolute mess for cable management and I was right. It is nice that it includes the Lighting Node Pro but this creates even more of a mess for cable management. I'll be honest, I gave up and I'm scared to look back to see how bad it looks like now.

If you are looking for performance over RGB, I definitely would not recommend these fans. You're paying for the Corsair branding and for iCUE. If you don't care about RGB, look at fans from Noctua. Way better performance and quality for a fraction of the price of these fans.

I will say that the RGB looks good but not 56$ per fan good. It is nice that it is customizable and able to sync with all other Corsair products especially if you're stuck in their ecosystem like I am. I've had the fans set to static teal since I received them and out of nowhere a few weeks ago, I noticed one of the sections of the fan turned blue instead of teal and this issue is also the same with other colours too.

I've been going back and forth with their customer service and I will say their customer service is pretty good considering what's going on in the world. As I said in the beginning, regardless if you have an issue with 1, 2 or all 3 fans, you will have to send all 3 fans back if you're having any issues. I'm currently in a situation where I do not have any extra fans and I need to use my computer for work but without the 3 fans, my computer will be unusable due to temps. We haven't found a solution to this yet and I'll make sure to update this review once all of this is over.

review_title: Decent picture quality, mediocre viewing angles but the worst monitor stand I've ever seen.
reviews:
I've been gaming on a TV for a while now and wanted to switch over to a monitor instead. Amazon Warehouse had this monitor on sale for around 115$ I believe so figured I'd give it a shot and I regret it.

The picture on the monitor is okay but the viewing angles definitely have some room for improvement especially this being an IPS panel.

I've loved ASUS as a company for years now but I'm so disappointed in them for even selling this monitor with the stand it comes with. I'm not sure if they collaborated with AliExpress or a local dollar store but the quality of the stand that comes with this monitor is absolutely HORRIBLE. It's built horribly, looks cheap and very wobbly.

If I had a rating to give the monitor on its own, it'd give it a 3 star but because of the stand, I have to give it a 2 star. Do yourself a favour and get a BenQ monitor, you'll definitely be happy with that.

review_title: Absolutely no grip to the mouse pad, feels cheap and horrible traction.
reviews:
I bought this mouse pad to replace this old mouse pad I got years ago after buying a keyboard and I'm very disappointed with my purchase.

The quality of this mouse pad is SIGNIFICANTLY worse than that old cheap free mouse pad I had. The traction is horrible and with the poor grip the mouse pad has, you will basically be moving your mouse pad around with your mouse.

I do not recommend this product what so ever.

I've been trying to find a good cleaner for a while now and I've finally found it! While the Epsom Salt and isopropyl method works very well, it always leaves a horrible taste after cleaning it and I normally have to let it sit overnight for the taste to go away.

This product is great! Good price, doesn't require a lot of the cleaner to do a deep clean, smells great and does not leave an after taste.

If you're looking for a good cleaner, I highly recommend Orange Chronic Cleaner! If one of my pieces get really dirty, I'll update this review to post a before and after picture!

EDIT: While I love the connivence of Amazon Prime, this package deal is actually more expensive than if you bought 2 bottles individually in a smoke shop. I went to 2 different shops in my area and they were all selling 16oz bottles for 16$ each.

review_title: Stopped working after a month and terrible customer service.
reviews:
While the mouse looks and feels good, I'm very disappointed in Razer. They promote how amazing their "Hyperspeed Connection" is but it's god awful. For the last year, I've been using this cheap $20 wireless mouse from some Chinese company for work and I've never had a connection with it. You'd imagine this $80 mouse with their "Hyperspeed Connection" to be even better right? Well, wrong. I consistently have issues with the mouse freezing on me and/or disconnecting whether I'm on Hyperspeed or Bluetooth mode.

The battery life isn't horrible but it isn't amazing either. I really wish they would have gone with a USB charger instead of batteries but in the end, it's not a huge deal. I had to replace the battery once in about a month of fairly heavy usage which I can't complain about.

Now, the main issue is that the right-click button keeps glitching out and makes it nearly impossible to use it in an FPS game like Call of Duty.

I've reached out to Razer last week regarding this and I've yet to get an answer from them. Even if they're willing to replace this one, I definitely do not plan on purchasing any of their wireless products again.

review_title: This should be included for free when purchasing a monitor from MSI.
reviews:
I recently purchased a 27" MSI G27C2 monitor from Canada Computers and I've been thrilled with it until now.
To start making some room on my desk, I wanted to mount the monitor on my wall. I went ahead, purchased a monitor mount for around 40$-50$ and once it came in, that was when I realized I wasn't able to mount it as there is no included VESA adapter when I purchased the monitor.

Now, this is my fault for not checking that when I purchased my monitor but come on MSI... I paid 80$ for my old monitor and it came with a VESA adapter so why is it my 300$ monitor doesn't come with one? The fact that this metal plate costs 40$ just shows that this is a pure money grab and they're looking to grab as much money as possible from their customers.

The plate does what it needs to do but I definitely do not plan on purchasing or recommending any more products from MSI. Seriously disappointed.

review_title: Took forever to setup, begins flickering when the light is OFF and it won’t let me return.
reviews:
Before writing a negative review, I always want to give it a chance but after trying for 2 days, I’ve given up with giving these lights a chance.

They say just to turn your lights on and off a few times, it’ll make the light start blinking which meant it’s ready to be paired. Well this took me an hour to get ONE of the lights connected because it kept telling me that there was a connection error. Once it was connected, everything worked fine. The light was bright, great colours but the app is a little bit slow which isn’t a big deal. I kept trying with the 2nd light to work but I ended up giving up for the night.

While I’m watching TV last night, the light are turned off but out of nowhere the lights just started flickering on and off with a bunch of different colours (seen in the video I’ve attached to this review).

Considering this product has great reviews, I’m very disappointed. I didn’t want to give it a 1 star because when it works, the light is fine and it seems like it works for a lot of other people but I’m just disappointed on what I received. To put icing on the cake, this product doesn’t have a refund/return option on this order so I guess I’m stuck with these non-functioning lights.

Purchased for my friend's kid's birthday because he loves Marvel and always drinks water from coffee mugs acting like it's coffee to be like his parents. His kid is absolutely obsessed with this mug and carries it around with him everywhere.

The mug is big which puts a big of weight on it, high quality print and easy to wash.

review_title: Great quality, doesn't move around on belt and fits Peerless and S&W perfectly.
reviews:
I've used a few different types of open handcuff pouches from different companies (Aker, Uzi and a few different small companies) and after using these for a year, this pouch has to be the best one. I like to keep both my handcuffs on my back and I never had any sort of issues with these comfort wise even when sitting down. The pouch is great quality, fits both my Peerless and Smith & Wesson chain handcuffs (not ASP unfortunately) perfectly and once they're in, they're in. There has not been a single incident where they came out accidentally.

If you're looking for an open handcuff pouch, I highly recommend these.
Love these
Great
Love it
Love them
No complaints
Super long and exactly what I needed
Great condition
It’s perfect!
Love everything about it!!!

I loved everything about it, until I washed it.
I followed the instructions on properly washing it and now it looks like there’s dirt stains ALL over it.
I’m assuming from the green leaking out! Very disappointment :( I was super excited to wear this out, but too gross looking to wear out in public

review_title: Gets ridiculously hot when it's plugged in and doesn't even get recognized
reviews: Bought this for my camera for work. After hours of footage, it didn't even save any of it. When I plugged it into my Macbook, it didn't get recognized. Bought one of those MicroSD USB readers from Anker (bought countless products from them and never had an issue) and it still doesn't work but within seconds, the card gets so hot that you can't even keep your finger on it. Thought it was maybe the USB readers fault but I tried other SD cards and it works perfectly fine. I definitely do not recommend this to anyone.

review_title: Extremely uncomfortable but they do their job.
reviews:
While these work perfectly as intended, they’re extremely uncomfortable. The clips are a thick metal that dig into your leg and the leather quality is at most mediocre.

I’d definitely recommend KK&Jay over these.

review_title: This has already saved someone’s life!
reviews:
I’m not happy that I’ve used this but it has come in handy countless times while working security and first aid. It’s always kept an accurate rating and has actually saved someone’s life.

While working security, we received a call about a female that collapsed. After placing the oximeter on her, we realized she had overdosed and her heart rate was dropping tremendously. Naloxone was issued and she was later brought to the hospital safely!

review_title: Awesome packaging, great fit and very comfortable!
reviews: Very comfortable, great fit and I can’t see it underneath my dress shirts! Also, I absolutely love the packaging! I love when a company puts that extra effort in their products like this.

review_title: Great quality, fit and comfort but received them worn.
reviews:
These are my 2nd pair of double monk straps from Stacy Adams and I love them. Very comfortable, looks awesome, great quality and all for a great price.

My issue is I received these used and was never informed they were used. The toe of both chooses were creased and the sole was dirty. I’m not complaining too much because they were nearly 50% off but they shouldn’t be selling shoes that are used and not informing the customer about it.
I decided to place the patch on my backpack and I’m thrilled with the way it looks. The velcro and stitching is very high quality!
love everything about it
accidentally bought the wrong size but was able to fix that with a friend of mine. love the product itself!
very wide but thats my fault because I didnt read it properly. otherwise product itself is great
love it! didn't realize I didnt have a plug In my hallway for it but thats a me problem lol product itself is great!

The socks are very comfortable but they’re not durable at all. After 1 wash I noticed a pair started to fray. After 3 washes one of the socks already had a rip in it.
Extremely disappointed with Under Armour.
These are unbelievably comfortable and great quality. Definitely going to be purchasing more pairs.
love them! beautiful colour!
exactly what we needed! would definitely recommend!
works great just too short for what we need

review_title: After 6 months, it's held up fantastic!
reviews:
Decided to hold off on writing a review about the belt until I used it enough. Purchased this belt in the beginning of November and I've probably put in over 1000 hours of use with this belt and there's little to no signs of wear and tear.

My only complaint about the belt is it's very stiff. It's really hard trying to adjust the sizing or even trying to put pouches on or off. Once you have everything setup though, you'll be extremely happy with it!

review_title: Holds up extremely well even after being used for a year.
reviews: I've had my backup flashlight (Coast G45) in this pouch for a year now and it's shown absolutely no signs of wear. This is potentially the most durable pouch I currently have on my belt and I couldn't be any happier. Highly recommend!

This is my 3rd Pop Socket now and again I'm very happy with the product. Very easy to install and gives you a better grip of your phone without making it feel uncomfortable. Highly recommend purchasing one!

You seriously can't go wrong with this. They don't cause any sort of discolouration on the screen, they're very easy to install and if you mess up 1 of them, you've got 5 other ones. For 10$ you seriously can't go wrong with this.

Absolutely love this shirt. Very comfortable, breathable, the fit is perfect and the quality is great. After multiple washes, the shirt hasn't shrunk at all and the materials still feel the same as when I received it. Definitely will be buying another one in the future.

review_title: Great scale but issues measuring under .3 grams
reviews: The scale is very small and easy to use. My only issue is when it comes to something that weighs less than .3 grams, it sometimes doesn't pick it up. You'll have to place whatever you have that weighs that much before turning it on and then move it to get a sense of how much it weighs. Aside from that, it's a great scale. Definitely will still give it a 5 star
Packaging was actually really nice considering the price. The cutter itself does it's job perfectly so you can't go wrong with that.

I kept having issues with my shirt untucking and I've heard really good things about wearing suspenders for your duty belt. Well, they were right. These suspenders are a lifesaver. My shirt stays tucked in during my entire shift, duty belt doesn't shift around and it also takes a lot of weight off of your belt. I personally wasn't too much of a fan of the shoulder pads so I ended up taking them off. They are removable which is great! Highly recommend these!

review_title: Size up! Great quality and fit.
reviews:
I've been wearing these pants for work for the last few weeks and they've been holding up great! Very comfortable, amazing fit and good materials. Really wish the back pockets had a button closure on it but it's not a big deal!
After reading the reviews, you definitely should size up though especially if you have bigger thighs and/or calves.
This pouch fits 2 dosses of Narcan perfectly. Quality is great and the velcro quality doesn't feel cheap.

Originally the headset was not working for my PS4 but after a few more attempts, it started working. For the price, this is a good headset. Very comfortable, decent on noice canceling, sound and microphone quality are good but not great. For 35$, you really can't go wrong.
bought the wrong item but had no problems returning it and it was in perfect condition
very happy with our purchase. its exactly what we needed
cleaning it off is a little difficult at times but it does its job very well!
I buy these on here cause I can never find them in store! My last one broke so they aren't the most durable but they definitely do their job!!
Found it a little pricey but honestly worth it. my laptop screen is so clean now!! and my keyboard too! would definitely recommend!

review_title: They really should emphasize the extra firm.
reviews: If you're looking for a go-to pillow for pillow fights, this is your best bet. When they say it's extra firm, they really mean it's EXTRA firm. It'll literally take a few seconds for the pillow to "shape" to your head while resting on it. It'll all come down to how firm you like your pillow but once it "shapes" to your head, it's very supportive and comfortable but that'll come down to your personnel preference.
The shirt has just the perfect fit. Tight around the arms but not skin tight and fitted throughout the rest of it. The material is also very soft and hasn't shrunk gotten frayed after a few washes.

review_title: Absolutely love them! Great fit and great quality.
reviews:
I've always loved the feel and fit of the Mechanix Wear Tactical Original Covert gloves regardless of the use for them. I loved using them working security but always had that worry in the back of my head about them not being cut resistant and ending up getting cut or poked with a dirty needle. These being a cut resistant palm really helps getting rid of that thought while maintaining the great feel and fit of the regular Covert gloves.

I highly recommend these gloves if you're in the law enforcement or security field.

review_title: Pouch is average quality but the velcro is not durable.
reviews: Purchased one of this pouch without the patch less than 4 months ago and the velcro wore out very quickly. I ended up ordering this one again basically because I knew it would fit on my vest properly and even though it's not going to last very long again, at least it comes with a Canada flag patch.

You can never go wrong with a pair of Peerless handcuffs whether it's chain or hinged. They're always great quality, have a great feel and aren't heavy. I personally do prefer S&W handcuffs more than Peerless due to their double locking mechanism but that's all personal preference.

review_title: Good material but wish they were slimmer and had better pockets.
reviews:
I'm giving them a 3 stars because of the amount of issues I've had with the pockets. The back pockets are wide and are diagonal with a small piece of velcro in the middle but no cover to them. There's been a few times now where my wallet has fallen out and I liked to have my knife attached to my back pocket but because it's diagonal, it always moves around or falls off. Compared to my old 5.11 pants, these cargo pockets fit very low. As it is getting something out of your front pocket while wearing a duty belt is hard but it's even harder with these pockets for some reason.

The pants themselves are good quality but I definitely would not consider them lightweight. I really wish they were slimmer as well. They were just way too baggy for my liking so I had to go get them tailored.

I'll still keep these pants in my rotation for work but I definitely will not be buying another pair.
Absolutely love the design of the controller!

review_title: Absolutely terrible smell when you get it but wash it once and you'll be happy!
reviews: When I purchase hoodies from Amazon and when I get them, they have this absolutely terrible smell of like vinegar. It's not a big deal because I always wash my new hoodies before wearing them but it's a fair warning for anyone! Asides from the smell, these hoodies are phenomenal. Cheap prices, great fit and tons of colors!
These pillows are so soft! I personally prefer a stiff pillow for my head but these make for great body pillows for me personally.
Bought this for a coworker during Christmas time and he absolutely loved it!

review_title: Not the greatest quality but has a great fit to it!
reviews: The hat has a great fit which is surprising but the low cost comes from the materials. The mesh on the back is very stiff and low quality which is what you should expect from an 8$ hat but for the price, you seriously can't go wrong.

It amazes me how this is only 50$. It has everything you need for such a low price. If you're looking for a streaming media player, this is your best bet. Not compares to this especially for the price.

I've bought a lot of things from 5.11, maybe too many but once again they knocked it out of the park. I've you've bought anything from 5.11 before, you know their products are great quality and this pouch is no different. It takes up just the right about of room on my vest and inside the pouch there's plenty of room for medical supplies and slots to organize everything.
This item has a very simple and sleek design which keeps my desk look more organized. For the price, you can’t go wrong.

review_title: Absolute essential for a duty belt.
reviews: I’ve yet to be disappointed by anything I’ve purchased from ZAK Tool. I was using a key silencer for a while but decided to try this out and I do not plan on ever going back. For the price, you can’t go wrong.

Decided to put my tourniquet on my belt instead of my vest. Out of all the pouches I tried, this one is by far the best.

I wear a 2.25” duty belt and once locked in, it doesn’t move at all. It’s very adjustable, fits my tourniquet perfectly and very high quality. I have it placed on my right side so it’s accessible for both hands but mostly my dominant side. I landed directly on the case and there wasn’t a single mark on it.

A little bit on the expensive side but definitely worth the money!
Bought this shirt for a friend as a Christmas gift. She absolutely loves it! Great fit and materials.

Still haven’t gotten used to not having a wallet in my back pocket so I’m constantly having mini heart attacks but it’s small and fits in my normal pockets perfectly. Materials don’t feel cheap and it holds all my cards I need comfortably. Highly recommend this product!
Bought this as a Christmas present for my cousin. She loves it! Definitely recommend this product.

I've purchased multiple items from Anker and I've yet to be disappointed. For the prices, they always exceed my expectations. The battery life is great, the charger itself charges quickly and charges my phone very quickly as well. The design is great, very simple and it's not huge but big enough to have a good battery life.

review_title: Great jacket besides the velcro on the wrist
reviews: Absolutely love the way the jacket fits and all the materials are great BUT the velcro on the wrist "straps". The velcro is cheap and never stays on so you'll constantly have to tighten the strap on your wrist over and over again.

review_title: Decent inexpensive knife but nothing crazy.
reviews: I wasn't expecting it to be this small but that's my fault not theirs. It may be the size but I'm not a huge fan of the way the "handle" feels. Doesn't really provide much grip or anything. Asides from that, it's a solid knife for the price. The materials aren't bad or anything but there's nothing spectacular about this knife either.

review_title: Came with a LOT of Hershey’s cookie and cream.
reviews: Everything tasted fine but it came with a LOT of the cookies and cream Hershey’s.
They’re made to write on and stick on whatever you stick them on and that’s exactly what they do. Not much else to say.
For less than 30$, you can’t go wrong. Does what a knife needs to do and doesn’t feel like it’s made out of cheap materials.

review_title: Simple, good quality and very bright!
reviews: Wasn’t looking for anything fancy. Wanted sometime simple that just turns on and off, very bright and good quality. This flashlight has a little button that has 5 brightness settings and an on/off button. Simple and easy.

review_title: Once again, 5.11 does a great job.
reviews: 5.11 does it again. Absolute no complaints about the pouch. Great materials and fits on my vest perfectly.

review_title: Not the greatest for thick nylon.
reviews: I wanted to put a few patches on my vest at work so decided to try these out. The vest is made out of a very thick nylon and it does stay on the vest but the corners tend to come loose every now and then.
The gloves fit great and they have great materials! Highly recommend!

review_title: Would be perfect if it didn’t have a weird smell.
reviews: The hold on the clay is awesome. Your hair doesn’t stay all stiff or shiny but it stays together throughout the day. My only complaint is the smell... I really can’t pinpoint what it smells like exactly but it’s definitely not great.
Not much to say. It tastes the exact same as it would taste if you bought it at a gas station or whoever.
This should be attached with everyone’s keys. Very easily could save your life if god forbid something were to happen where this would be needed to be used.

review_title: Very large opening on the back.
reviews: Leather is nice and the velcro hasn’t shown any signs of wear within the last few months I’ve had it. Only complaint is I don’t understand why the opening on the back is so big. It could fit a easily fit a 3” belt. The way I have it placed, it doesn’t move around a lot but it’s unnecessarily big.

review_title: One of the best earphones in this price range!
reviews:
The sound quality and noise canceling is top notch especially for the price. They’re great for casual wear and using them at the gym. They don’t fall out of your ears regardless if you’re running or jumping around.
My only complaint is the battery life. If I could give it a 3 1/2 star, I’d give it that. It really does not last that long.

review_title: Inaccurate body fat percentage, poor battery life and app is horrible.
reviews: This scale is not able to get an accurate number for your body fat percentage. The app is poorly organized and confusing. The battery life is also terrible.

I’ve owned a few items from Bianchi that have basketweave and the leather is always great quality. This case is no exception but it never stays closed! It always opened up regardless of where I keep it on my belt or whatever kind of handcuffs are in the case. Used it for a week and then immediately went back to open handcuff cases.

review_title: If you plan on putting a lot of stuff on your vest, stay away from this pouch.
reviews:
I purchased this pouch almost 6 months ago and loved it at first. I was carrying the 5.11 radio pouch, medical pouch and handcuff pouch on my molle vest and I had no issues with them aside from those 3 things taking up 8 slots on my vest but at the time that wasn't an issue as there wasn't anything I needed or wanted on my vest. The handcuff pouch is great quality and fits 2 handcuffs perfectly (hinged and/or chain).

About 4 months ago I decided it was probably time for me to start carrying a tourniquet with me again. I wanted to place it on my vest but unfortunately my 3 pouches literally took up my entire vest. Then I realized that the handcuff pouch literally takes up 4 slots on my vest. A radio pouch only takes up 2 slots so why should a handcuff pouch take 4 slots right? I decided to look around and I ending up finding multiple handcuff molle pouches that only take up 1-2 slots so I decided to switch over to another one (went with the HSG handcuff taco).

Now if you've got 4 slots on your vest to use for 1 pouch, I'd give this a 5/5. If you have or plan to have a decent amount of stuff on your vest, I definitely wouldn't go for this pouch.
There's not much else to say other than this product is perfect and an absolute essential.

I've bough 4 different shakers from Performa and they've all been great. I absolutely love Batman so of course I bought it. It was a great shaker until it broke. I might of had less than 1/5 of the bottle filled with water and accidentally dropped it which ended up cracking the entire bottom of the bottle.

review_title: You can really tell it's 12$ in the long run.
reviews:
Original Review: The pouch has great materials and fits a tourniquet perfectly. It'll always stay on my vest but I hope I'll never have to use it.

Updated Review: Purchased this pouch in mid November of 2018 and I carry it on my vest. Within the last 3 months, it really has shown why the pouch is only 12$. There are loose threads everywhere, the velcro is terrible quality, the pouch moves around like crazy and the snap always comes off.
It's got great materials and does exactly what a belt is meant to do.

I was using a pair of extremely old and worn out pair of handcuffs that my company issued me for a while so I went out and bought a pair of S&Ws a few months back and fell in love with them. Saw there was a sale going on with these so I figured I'd give them a shot.

They function like any regular pair of handcuffs. Make sure they're oiled and they'll be ready to go. They're not light like a pair of handcuffs from ASP but they don't weigh a ton either. I absolutely love the black oxide look compared to the nickel finish. The only reason why I don't give them a 5 star is because after using S&W handcuffs, I can't stand using the double lock mechanism on these.

My dog was always picking at his paws after walks because of all of the salt and snow so I decided to try these out. I knew immediately he was going to hate me when I put them on him but after a bit of walking, he's perfectly fine. I wish I would of went a size larger but the mediums work well enough to not have to do the entire return process!

review_title: Absolutely love these handcuffs but they rust very easily.
reviews:
After over 6 months of heavy usage, I figured it'd be time for an updated review.

When I was originally looking around to purchase my first set of handcuffs for work, the immediate question was Peerless or Smith & Wesson? I ended up purchasing a pair of S&W Model 100s as my primary and also a pair of Peerless M-700s as my secondary.

The S&Ws and M-700s both have their ups and downs. I much prefer the S&Ws because of the two-sided double lock mechanism. Personally I've found that to be extremely helpful when it comes to placing these on someone who is combative and/or resistant. When it comes to applying them on someone, both are very smooth but I find the M-700s are a lot smoother.

After reviewing a majority of the reviews on the Canadian and American Amazon, I think we can all agree on 1 thing. These rust very easily and you can't hide it when they rust. I've basically always used open handcuff pouches and with the handcuffs being exposed to a lot of snow and rain, they definitely began rusting but it's only a visual issue because I've yet to see a slight difference in performance.

If you're looking to purchase handcuffs for work, please do your research because there are many companies (Peerless, S&W, ASP) and different kinds of handcuffs (chained, hinged, rigid). If you're leaning towards a pair of S&Ws, I'd definitely recommend getting these in their nickel finish.

review_title: Decent quality but not made for law enforcement.
reviews:
I’ve been using Smith and Wesson Model 100’s for nearly a year now so I was curious to see how an inexpensive pair of handcuffs would preform.

Unlocking the handcuffs with a paper clip can be done by someone with zero to little no experience how to do it due to how big the key hole is compared to a normal pair. Plus the chain feels like a very cheap/weak steel.

This is the biggest deal breaker for me. Zak Tools have keys that give you access to the double locking mechanism and key hole to nearly every single handcuff model out there BUT these ones because the double lock hole is nearly half the size of the size of a pair of Smith and Wesson or Peerless. There’s nothing I hate more than having to be forced to use the regular small handcuff key.

Now, I would recommend these for any kind of use besides that. As long as you’re not using these for law enforcement, they’re a decent pair of handcuffs.

The fit of the gloves are horrible. I've wear large in all my gloves but I can't go up or down a size. The gloves are loose at places and skin tight at others and the fingers are very narrow and tapered. What makes everything worse is how uncomfortable they are. Leather is cheap and by putting a little bit of pressure with a pocket knife, it went straight through the glove.

review_title: Flashlight is terrible but the knife was great.
reviews: The flashlight was absolutely terrible. Those pictures definitely can not be actual pictures of that flashlight being used. On the other hand though, the knife was great. No complaints at all about the knife.
Pretty comfortable hat but gets a little irritating after about 2 hours of wears.
Really great sound quality and very simple to use. No wonder it's one of Amazon's Choices!
Flashlight broke in less than 2 months. Really not happy.
Great watch, use it nearly every day at work. Has everything I need, it's comfortable and cheap!
Great clock! No complaints.

review_title: ... a shot and I was really surprised on how good it was
reviews: I honestly purchased this book by accident but decided to give it a shot and I was really surprised on how good it was. Highly recommend if you're a fan of his music!
Not the greatest quality but for less than 20$, you can't really go wrong.

review_title: My work boots began to smell just horrible so I figured I'd give it a shot since ...
reviews: My work boots began to smell just horrible so I figured I'd give it a shot since it had some good reviews but sadly it didn't do a thing. It honestly made it worse. I gave it a 3/5 instead of a 2/5 because maybe it's simply because my boots are just too old now and need to be replaced.
